{
  "_documentation": "OCP Console compat: every panel + target + templating var uses literal \"datasource\": \"prometheus\" (NOT a ${DS_PROMETHEUS} template variable) because OCP Console's built-in dashboard renderer does NOT evaluate Grafana templating variables of type=datasource. Original Grafana export had `{type: prometheus, uid: ${DS_PROMETHEUS}}` everywhere — that pattern silently breaks all panels in Console. Phase 2 polish (intentionally empty panels, see demo-manifests/README.md): panel 3 (polygon_errors_total — registered, never incremented under healthy operation), panel 5 (kafka_consumergroup_lag — needs Strimzi spec.kafkaExporter sidecar), panel 8 (kube_deployment_status_replicas_ready — kube-state-metrics is in platform Prometheus, not UWM). All 14 keynote-relevant entropy + window-compute panels populate without those fixes.",
  "annotations": {
    "list": [
      {
        "builtIn": 1,
        "datasource": {"type": "grafana", "uid": "-- Grafana --"},
        "enable": true,
        "hide": true,
        "iconColor": "rgba(0, 211, 255, 1)",
        "name": "Annotations & Alerts",
        "type": "dashboard"
      },
      {
        "datasource": "prometheus",
        "enable": true,
        "expr": "ALERTS{alertname=~\"PolygonFeedStalled|UlyssesEntropySpike|UlyssesConsumerLagHigh\",alertstate=\"firing\"}",
        "iconColor": "red",
        "name": "Ulysses alerts",
        "titleFormat": "{{alertname}}",
        "tagKeys": "severity,alertname",
        "textFormat": "{{ticker}}"
      }
    ]
  },
